# Lab 06 Practice Case Brief

## Case: RSU Nexus – Campus Resource Marketplace

Many students have unused textbooks, electronics, study materials, and other items that could be sold or shared with other students. However, existing methods such as social media groups or informal messaging are unorganized, making it difficult to find reliable listings, communicate with sellers, and manage transactions safely within the campus community.

## Target Users

- Student who wants to sell or offer a campus resource
- Student who wants to buy or obtain a campus resource
- Admin who manages listings and monitors marketplace activities

## Product Direction

A web-based campus marketplace that allows students to post resource listings, browse available items, search and filter listings, view detailed information, communicate with sellers through private messaging, track listing status (Available, Reserved, Sold), and enables administrators to manage listings and users.

## Lab 06 Focus

Use this project as the group case. Apply the software engineering process by identifying requirements, designing wireframes, creating user flows, implementing the prototype, and testing the core marketplace functionalities based on the project requirements.
